SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A mixture of allergens obtained from animals.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Domestic Cat Dander Antigen;Felis catus Dander Antigen
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An animal allergen in the form of dander (skin flakes) produced by the species Felis catus (domestic cat).

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Bos taurus Dander Antigen;Cattle Dander Antigen
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An animal allergen in the form of dander (skin flakes) produced by the species Bos taurus (cow).

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Canis familiaris Dander Antigen;Canis lupus familiaris Dander Antigen
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An animal allergen in the form of dander (skin flakes) produced by the species Canis lupus familiaris (dog).

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Domestic Horse Dander Antigen;Equus caballus Dander Antigen
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An animal allergen in the form of dander (skin flakes) produced by the species Equus caballus (domestic horse).
A group of autoimmune substances found in the nucleus of a cell that are the target of autoantibodies.
An autoantigen encoded by the Ro52 gene (also called the TRIM21 gene) and has a molecular weight of 52 kDa. It is associated with the autoimmune disease Sjogrens Syndrome.
An autoantigen encoded by the Ro60 gene and has a molecular weight of 60 kDa. It is associated with the autoimmune disease Sjogrens Syndrome.
An autoantigen encoded by the SSB gene. It is associated with the autoimmune disease Sjogrens Syndrome.
